---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout lang="en" title="Privacy" path="privacy/">
  <article class="legal">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-meta">Last updated 6 July 2026</p>

    <p>
      This policy explains what personal data Dove Go collects and how we use it, under the EU
      General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
    </p>

    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Your email address</strong> — to sign you in and send you one-time sign-in links.</li>
      <li><strong>Events you submit</strong> — the content you provide (title, description, dates, venue, images).</li>
      <li>
        <strong>A session cookie</strong> — a single essential cookie that keeps you signed in. No
        advertising or third-party tracking cookies are used.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Why, and our lawful basis</h2>
    <p>
      We use your email solely to authenticate you (our legitimate interest in providing a secure,
      account-based service, and to perform the service you request). We do not sell your data or
      use it for advertising. Sign-in emails are delivered through Resend; event data and your
      account are stored on Cloudflare infrastructure in the EU region.
    </p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep your account while it is active. Sign-in links expire within minutes. You can ask us
      to delete your account and personal data at any time.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to access, correct or delete your personal data, to object to or restrict
      processing, and to data portability. To exercise any of these, or to complain, email
      <a href="mailto:public@dovego.it">public@dovego.it</a>. You may also complain to your local data
      protection authority (in Italy, the Garante per la protezione dei dati personali).
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy; the date above reflects the latest version.</p>
  </article>
</Layout>
